{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8aac8f31-ab3c-450b-8fd0-a92e6d0be514","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `sos threads` — list managed threads\n\n**Using `lldb` (Linux/macOS):**\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load /path/to/libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\nsos ClrStack\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg (Windows):**\nLoad the dump, then use `!analyze -v` and `!pe`.\n\nWould you like me to walk you through any of these steps in more detail, or do you have `dotnet-dump` installed so we can try analyzing the file here?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"763dddb1-7563-4fc9-a2bc-d3c0c243e4c3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for collecting/configuring crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I should NOT invoke that skill. Instead, I'll provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"2056:39211A:75DB98:89408A:69F01359"},"id":"76fe7b86-65cf-4775-8ea1-96bb669c8718","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:54:43.564Z","parentId":"cf81e786-ae30-4373-9ae4-180a24f03a6e"}
